vier|date=|website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Reynolds4March2020\">{{Cite news|last=Reynolds|first=Matt|url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic?|date=4 March 2020|work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|issn=1357-0978}}</ref>\n\nUnlike [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]], the [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 <ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\">{{cite web|url=https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus|website=Imperial News|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Gov.ukHCIDDef\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England|last=|first=|date=|website=GOV.UK|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> has been much lower, but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=\"WFSA\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus|last=|first=|date=|website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\" /> COVID-19 typically appears with about seven days of [[Influenza-like illness|flu-like symptoms]] followed by some people progressing to symptoms of a [[viral pneumonia]] requiring admission to hospital.<ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\" /> From 19 March, COVID-19 was no longer classified as a \"High consequence infectious disease\".<ref name=\"Gov.ukHCIDDef\" />\n\n== Timeline ==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Romania medical cases chart}}\n\n=== 21 February\u20132 March: First preventive measures ===\nOn 21 February, following a [[2020 coronavirus outbreak in Italy|COVID-19 outbreak in Italy]], the Romanian government announced a 14-day quarantine for citizens returning from the affected regions.<ref name=\"rri.ro\" />\n\nOn 22 February, the Romanian government announced several preventive measures including designation of five hospitals as isolation centers for new cases, purchase and placement of thermal scanners in international airports and specially designated lines for passengers coming from areas affected by COVID-19 outbreak.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://stirileprotv.ro/stiri/actualitate/primele-masuri-anuntate-de-romania-pentru-a-preveni-aparitia-noului-virus-din-china.html |title=Primele m\u0103suri anun\u021bate de Rom\u00e2nia pentru a preveni apari\u021bia noului virus din China |website=\u0218tirile Pro TV |language=ro |trans-title=The first measures announced by Romania to prevent the emergence of the new virus from China |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200122154712/https://stirileprotv.ro/stiri/actualitate/primele-masuri-anuntate-de-romania-pentru-a-preveni-aparitia-noului-virus-din-china.html |archive-date=22 January 2020 |access-date=22 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://stirileprotv.ro/stiri/international/epidemia-din-china-posibilitatea-ca-noul-coronavirus-sa-ajunga-in-romania.html |title=Epidemia din China. Posibilitatea ca noul coronavirus s\u0103 ajung\u0103 \u00een Rom\u00e2nia |website=\u0218tirile Pro TV |language=ro |trans-title=Epidemic from China. The possibility of the coronavirus to arrive in Romania |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128011648/https://stirileprotv.ro/stiri/international/epidemia-din-china-posibilitatea-ca-noul-coronavirus-sa-ajunga-in-romania.html |archive-date=28 January 2020 |access-date=27 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://stirileprotv.ro/stiri/sanatate/romania-ia-noi-masuri-in-urma-epidemiei-din-china-ce-se-va-intampla-pe-aeroporturi.html |title=Rom\u00e2nia ia noi m\u0103suri \u00een urma epidemiei din China. Ce se va \u00eent\u00e2mpla pe aeroporturi |website=\u0218tirile Pro TV |language=ro |trans-title=Romania takes new measures following the China epidemic. What will happen in airports |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127214840/https://stirileprotv.ro/stiri/sanatate/romania-ia-noi-masuri-in-urma-epidemiei-din-china-ce-se-va-intampla-pe-aeroporturi.html |archive-date=27 January 2020 |access-date=27 January 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"rri.ro\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.rri.ro/en_gb/measures_against_the_coronavirus-2612485 |title=Radio Romania International - Measures against the coronavirus |website=Radio Romania International |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226012921/https://www.rri.ro/en_gb/measures_against_the_coronavirus-2612485 |archive-date=26 February 2020 |access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 February, new measures were imposed. Upon arrival on the Romanian territory, all asymptomatic travelers from the affected areas, respectively [[Hubei]], the 11 localities in [[Italy]], and any remaining passengers on the [[Diamond Princess (ship)|Diamond Princess]] cruise ship will go directly to the quarantine, for a period for 14 days. The other people coming from the Lombardy and Veneto regions will enter voluntary isolation at home for 14 days, upon arrival in Romania.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ms.ro/2020/02/25/continuarea-masurile-de-prevenire-si-limitare-a-eventualelor-imbolnaviri-cu-noul-coronavirus/ |title=Continuarea m\u0103surile de prevenire \u0219i limitare a eventualelor \u00eemboln\u0103viri cu noul coronavirus \u2013 Ministerul S\u0103n\u0103t\u0103\u021bii |language=ro-RO |url-status=live |access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 February, the Minister of Education and Research required schools to spread awareness about coronavirus.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.hotnews.ro/stiri-educatie-23685876-ministerul-educatiei-10-sfaturi-pentru-elevii-profesorii-fereasca-infectia-provocata-coronavirus.htm |title=Coronavirus: Zece sfaturi pentru elevi \u0219i profesori - Ministerul Educa\u021biei - Educatie - HotNews.ro |date=2020-02-26 |website=www.hotnews.ro |language=ro |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227160307/https://www.hotnews.ro/stiri-educatie-23685876-ministerul-educatiei-10-sfaturi-pentru-elevii-profesorii-fereasca-infectia-provocata-coronavirus.htm |archive-date=27 February 2020 |access-date=2020-03-05}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ms.ro/coronavirus-covid-19/ |title=Coronavirus (Covid-19) \u2013 Ministerul S\u0103n\u0103t\u0103\u021bii |language=ro-RO |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304133644/http://www.ms.ro/coronavirus-covid-19/ |archive-date=4 March 2020 |access-date=2020-03-05}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 February, the [[Romanian Orthodox Church]] suggested that followers use their own spoons and avoid the traditional kissing of icons in church.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://orthodoxtimes.com/romanian-church-takes-action-against-coronavirus-to-reduce-transmission-through-holy-communion-and-kissing/ |title=Romanian Church takes action against coronavirus to reduce transmission through Holy Communion and kissing |date=February 28, 2020 |access-date=10 March 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309162738/https://orthodoxtimes.com/romanian-church-takes-action-against-coronavirus-to-reduce-transmission-through-holy-communion-and-kissing/ |archive-date=9 March 2020 |agency=Orthodox Times}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 March, more preventive measures were taken by the National Committee for Special Emergency Situations. Thus, citizens arriving from other provinces or cities in [[mainland China]], other localities in [[Lombardy]], [[Veneto]] or [[Emilia-Romagna]] regions of [[Italy]], as well as areas and localities in [[South Korea]] and [[Iran]] not previously specified for institutionalised quarantine, enter 14 days of self-isolation at home immediately upon returning to Romania.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ms.ro/2020/03/02/buletin-informativ-02-03-2020-ora-16-00/ |title=Buletin informativ 02.03.2020, ora 16.00 |date=2 March 2020 |website=Ministry of Health |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308221520/http://www.ms.ro/2020/03/02/buletin-informativ-02-03-2020-ora-16-00/ |archive-date=8 March 2020 |access-date=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== 8\u201312 March: Public gatherings banned, schools suspended ===\nOn 8 March, the Head of the Department for Emergency Situations, [[Raed Arafat]], announced a ban on all indoor or outdoor activities involving the participation of more than 1,000 people (these numbers were subsequently changed, see below). These restrictions are valid until 31 March, when a new assessment will be made.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ziare.com/stiri/coronavirus/masuri-anti-coronavirus-in-romania-sunt-interzise-activitatile-care-aduna-mai-mult-de-1-000-de-persoane-1600747 |title=M\u0103suri anti-coronavirus \u00een Rom\u00e2nia: Sunt interzise activit\u0103\u021bile cu mai mult de 1.000 de persoane |date=8 March 2020 |website=Ziare.com |language=ro |trans-title=Anti-coronavirus measures in Romania: Activities with more than 1000 people are forbidden |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309154009/http://www.ziare.com/stiri/coronavirus/masuri-anti-coronavirus-in-romania-sunt-interzise-activitatile-care-aduna-mai-mult-de-1-000-de-persoane-1600747 |archive-date=9 March 2020 |access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> After [[Northern Italy]] [[2020 Italy coronavirus lockdown|was put under quarantine on 8 March]], low-cost airline [[Wizz Air]] suspended all flights to [[Treviso]] and [[Bergamo]] until 3 April. Likewise, [[Blue Air]] cancelled all flights to and from [[Milan]] for 8 and 9 March. In the same day, flights from and to Italy have been suspended.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mediafax.ro/coronavirus/wizz-air-suspenda-toate-zborurile-din-romania-spre-nordul-italiei-din-cauza-epidemiei-de-covid-19-ce-face-blue-air-18947675 |title=Wizz Air suspend\u0103 toate zborurile din Rom\u00e2nia spre nordul Italiei din cauza epidemiei de COVID-19 / Ce face Blue Air |last=Cadi\u0219, Anamaria |date=8 March 2020 |website=Mediafax |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309222257/https://www.mediafax.ro/coronavirus/wizz-air-suspenda-toate-zborurile-din-romania-spre-nordul-italiei-din-cauza-epidemiei-de-covid-19-ce-face-blue-air-18947675 |archive-date=9 March 2020 |access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/ministii-marcel-vela-si-victor-costache-fac-declaratii-de-presa-la-ministerul-de-interne-la-ora-23-30-1272271 |title=Rom\u00e2nia suspend\u0103 zborurile din \u0219i c\u0103tre Italia |date=2020-03-08 |website=Digi24 |language=ro |trans-title=Romania suspends flights from and to Italy |access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref> In a press conference, Interior Minister Marcel Vela stated that if a school reports even a case, courses will be suspended throughout the school.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.romania-insider.com/romania-unprecedented-measures-stop-coronavirus-march-2020 |title=Romania announces unprecedented measures to prevent coronavirus spreading |date=8 March 2020 |website=Romania Insider |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 March, the officials announced the cessation of flights to and from Italy, at all airports in the country, until 23 March.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/ministii-marcel-vela-si-victor-costache-fac-declaratii-de-presa-la-ministerul-de-interne-la-ora-23-30-1272271 |title=Rom\u00e2nia suspend\u0103 zborurile din \u0219i c\u0103tre Italia |website=www.digi24.ro |language=ro |access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref> On the same day, the National Committee for Special Emergency Situations has decided to close all schools in Romania, starting on 11 March until 22 March, with the possibility of extending the measure. All bus rides and rail transport to and from Italy were suspended from 10 March until 31 March.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/toate-scolile-din-romania-se-inchid-din-10-martie-pana-dupa-paste-1272588 |title=OFICIAL. Toate \u0219colile din Rom\u00e2nia vor fi \u00eenchise \u00eencep\u00e2nd de miercuri p\u00e2n\u0103 pe 22 martie, cu posibilitatea de prelungire a m\u0103surii |date=2020-03-09 |website=Digi24 |language=ro |trans-title=OFFICIAL. All schools from Romania will be closed starting on Wednesday until 22 March, with the possibility of extending the measure |access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://adevarul.ro/news/societate/covid-19-Scolile-inchid-timp-saptamana-incepand-miercuri-1_5e6672345163ec4271d3300e/index.html |title=E oficial. \u0218colile se \u00eenchid timp de 11 zile, \u00eencep\u00e2nd de miercuri. Cursele feroviare \u0219i auto vor fi verificate pe grani\u021b\u0103 |date=2020-03-09 |website=www.adevarul.ro |language=ro |trans-title=It's official. Schools are closing for 11 days, starting on Wednesday. Railroad and auto rides will be checked at border |access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref> The Committee also decided to establish a series of obligations for food units and for public and private providers of passenger transport, such as frequent disinfection of surfaces, avoiding crowds in commercial spaces, frequent disinfection of the passenger compartment in the means of transport, etc.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ms.ro/2020/03/10/buletin-informativ-10-03-2020-ora-1000/ |title=Buletin informativ 10.03.2020, ora 10:00 |date=10 March 2020 |website=Ministry of Health}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 March, the Government published a list of fifteen guidelines regarding the \"responsible social behavior in preventing the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19)\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mai.gov.ro/15-recomandari-privind-conduita-sociala-responsabila-in-prevenirea-raspandirii-coronavirus-covid-19/ |title=15 RECOMAND\u0102RI privind conduita social\u0103 responsabil\u0103 \u00een prevenirea r\u0103sp\u00e2ndirii coronavirus (COVID-19) |date=11 March 2020 |website=Ministry of Internal Affairs}}</ref> The authorities have imposed a ban on sports, scientific, religious, cultural or entertainment events with over 100 participants in closed spaces until 31 March.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ziare.com/stiri/coronavirus/toate-evenimentele-cu-peste-100-de-persoane-in-spatii-inchise-sunt-interzise-inclusiv-slujbele-din-biserici-1601168 |title=Toate evenimentele cu peste 100 de persoane \u00een spa\u021bii \u00eenchise sunt interzise! Inclusiv, slujbele din biserici |last=Dioche\u021banu, Andreea |date=11 March 2020 |website=Ziare.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312163942/http://www.ziare.com/stiri/coronavirus/toate-evenimentele-cu-peste-100-de-persoane-in-spatii-inchise-sunt-interzise-inclusiv-slujbele-din-biserici-1601168 |archive-date=12 March 2020 |access-date=12 March 2020}}</ref> Likewise, the public activities for museums were suspended until 31 March.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/restrictii-noi-in-romania-din-cauza-covid-19-activitatile-culturale-religioase-si-de-divertisment-cu-peste-100-de-persoane-interzise-1273667 |title=Restric\u021bii noi \u00een Rom\u00e2nia din cauza COVID-19. Activit\u0103\u021bile culturale, religioase \u0219i de divertisment cu peste 100 de persoane, interzise |date=11 March 2020 |website=Digi 24}}</ref>\n[[File:STSB Coronavirus.jpg|thumb|left|200px| Voluntari - Bucharest bus route with interdiction for passengers in the driver's area]]\nOn 12 March, Serbian authorities have closed seven border points with Romania to prevent the spread of coronavirus.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.hotnews.ro/stiri-esential-23718097-coronavirus-serbia-inchis-mai-multe-puncte-frontiera-romania.htm |title=Coronavirus: Serbia a \u00eenchis mai multe puncte de frontier\u0103 cu Rom\u00e2nia |date=12 March 2020 |website=HotNews.ro}}</ref> On the same day, the [[Romanian Ombudsman]] asked President [[Klaus Iohannis]] to declare the state of emergency and the [[Parliament of Romania|Romanian Parliament]] to approve it. In a televised statement, the Secretary of State in the Ministry of Health, {{ill|Nelu T\u0103taru|ro}}, said that the current situation does not impose such an extreme measure.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ziare.com/stiri/coronavirus/avocatul-poporului-cere-declararea-starii-de-urgenta-1601344 |title=Avocatul Poporului cere declararea st\u0103rii de urgen\u021b\u0103 |date=12 March 2020 |website=Ziare.com}}</ref> The [[Romanian Football Federation]] decided to postpone all football matches in Romania until 31 March.<ref name=\"ziare\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ziare.com/fotbal/stiri-fotbal/coronavirusul-afecteaza-sportul-iata-ce-evenimente-au-fost-anulate-1601287 |title=Coronavirusul afecteaz\u0103 sportul: Toate meciurile de fotbal din Rom\u00e2nia au fost am\u00e2nate |date=12 March 2020 |website=Ziare.com}}</ref> Interior Minister Marcel Vela announced that the border crossing points with low traffic have been closed so that employees there to be directed to high traffic posts.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.g4media.ro/coronavirus-punctele-de-frontiera-cu-trafic-redus-au-fost-inchise-exportul-de-medicamente-si-echipamente-medicale-a-fost-stopat.html |title=Coronavirus: Punctele de frontier\u0103 cu trafic redus au fost \u00eenchise/ Exportul de medicamente \u0219i echipamente medicale a fost stopat |last=Budescu, Daniel |date=12 March 2020 |website=G4Media}}</ref> Health Minister [[Victor Costache]] issued an order prohibiting the export of medicines and medical equipment for six months.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://romania.europalibera.org/a/costache-suspend%C4%83-exportul-paralel-de-medicamente-vela-a-oprit-un-transport-la-grani%C8%9B%C4%83/30484431.html |title=Costache suspend\u0103 exportul paralel de medicamente. Vela a oprit mai multe transporturi la grani\u021b\u0103 |date=12 March 2020 |website=Radio Europa Liber\u0103 Rom\u00e2nia}}</ref>\n\n=== 13 March: First infected politician ===\nOn March 13, {{ill|Vergil Chi\u021bac|ro}}, former admiral, who acts as an independent in the PNL senators' group, was diagnosed with COVID-19. He isolated himself after finding out that a French parliamentarian, with whom he had been traveling to [[Brussels]], was found with coronavirus.<ref name=\"chitac\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.libertatea.ro/stiri/senatorul-vergil-chitac-confirmat-coronavirus-2911092 |title=Guvernul \u0219i PNL se izoleaz\u0103 dup\u0103 ce senatorul Vergil Chi\u021bac a fost confirmat cu coronavirus. El a participat luni la \u0219edin\u021bele de plen! |last=Postelnicu |first=Valentina |last2=Duca |first2=Dan |date=13 March 2020 |website=Libertatea}}</ref> On March 9, Chi\u021bac attended a party meeting with over 100 people. Parliamentary sources claim that he was also present in the Senate on March 12, when he attended the group and plenary sessions.<ref name=\"chitac\" /> In these conditions, all members of the National Political Bureau of PNL self-isolated at home. Interim Prime-minister [[Ludovic Orban]] announced that all PNL senators have an obligation to isolate themselves and that he will self-isolate at Vila Lac 1.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/guvernul-si-pnl-intra-in-autoizolare-1274762 |title=Guvernul \u0219i PNL intr\u0103 \u00een autoizolare dup\u0103 ce senatorul Vergil Chi\u021bac a fost confirmat cu coronavirus. PNL nu mai merge la consult\u0103ri |date=13 March 2020 |website=Digi 24}}</ref> He also announced that all ministers will be tested for coronavirus and self-isolate in their cabinets.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.hotnews.ro/stiri-politic-23721161-toata-conducerea-pnl-izoleaza-domiciliu-dupa-senator-liberal-fost-diagnosticat-covid-19-orban-voi-izola-vila-lac-1.htm |title=Coronavirus: Premierul se izoleaz\u0103 la Vila Lac / Toat\u0103 conducerea PNL se izoleaz\u0103 la domiciliu \u0219i to\u021bi mini\u0219trii vor fi testa\u021bi dup\u0103 ce un senator liberal a fost diagnosticat cu COVID-19 / Orban: L-am informat pe Iohannis |last=D., C. |date=13 March 2020 |website=HotNews.ro}}</ref>\n\n=== 14\u201321 March: State of emergency declared, parliamentary activity suspended ===\n[[File:Self-declaration regarding leaving the home - Coronavirus pandemic in Romania.jpg|thumb|220px|right|Self-declaration regarding leaving the home]]\n[[File:Dezinfectarea strazilor.jpg|thumb|220px|right|Disinfection in [[Bucharest]]]]\nOn March 14, after over 101 people have been diagnosed with coronavirus, [[Romania]] entered the third COVID-19 scenario.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/romania-a-depasit-pragul-de-100-de-persoane-infectate-cu-coronavirus-se-intra-in-scenariul-trei-pregatit-de-autoritati-1275455 |title=Rom\u00e2nia a dep\u0103\u0219it pragul de 100 de persoane infectate cu coronavirus. Se intr\u0103 \u00een scenariul al treilea, preg\u0103tit de autorit\u0103\u021bi |date=14 March 2020 |website=Digi24 |trans-title=Romania topped the limit of 100 people infected with coronavirus. It enters the third scenario, prepared by authorities |access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref> The third scenario goes from 101 to 2,000 cases. In the third scenario the doctors will perform epidemiological screening in the tents installed in the hospitals' yards, and the hospitals of infectious diseases will treat only cases of [[SARS-CoV-2]] infection.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mediafax.ro/coronavirus/romania-intra-in-scenariul-3-dupa-cazul-100-de-coronavirus-ce-presupune-acesta-18985736 |title=Rom\u00e2nia intr\u0103 \u00een scenariul 3, dup\u0103 cazul 100 de coronavirus. Ce presupune acesta |last=Foarfec\u0103, Eugenia |date=14 March 2020 |website=Mediafax}}</ref> Likewise, the authorities will be able to impose quarantine at home, not just in hospitals, as in many areas the capacities of medical units could be exceeded.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.libertatea.ro/stiri/cele-4-scenarii-de-lupta-impotriva-covid-19-2911142 |title=UPDATE. Scenariul 3 \u00een caz de coronavirus. Ce prev\u0103d cele 4 scenarii de lupt\u0103 \u00eempotriva COVID-19 |last=Pan\u0103, \u0218tefan |date=14 March 2020 |website=Libertatea}}</ref> At the same time, according to the plan in the third scenario, public gatherings with more than 50 people are banned.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/coronavirus-romania-sunt-interzise-adunarile-mai-mari-de-50-de-persoane-1275483 |title=Coronavirus Rom\u00e2nia, scenariul 3: Sunt interzise adun\u0103rile mai mari de 50 de persoane |date=14 March 2020 |website=Digi 24}}</ref> Three more [[National Liberal Party (Romania)|liberals]] have been diagnosed with COVID-19, all contacts of senator Vergil Chi\u021bac.<ref name=\"digi24.ro\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/politica/trei-liberali-infectati-de-senatorul-vergil-chitac-1275450 |title=Trei liberali, infecta\u021bi de senatorul Vergil Chi\u0163ac |date=14 March 2020 |website=Digi24 |language=ro |trans-title=Three liberals, infected by senator Vergil Chi\u021bac |access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref> [[Marcel Ciolacu]], President of the Chamber of Deputies, announced that the [[Parliament of Romania|Parliament]] will suspend its activity for a week. However, the activities will be carried out online.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/politica/parlamentarii-isi-suspenda-activitatea-pentru-cel-putin-o-saptamana-din-cauza-coronavirusului-1275427 |title=Parlamentarii \u00ee\u0219i suspend\u0103 activitatea pentru cel pu\u021bin o s\u0103pt\u0103m\u00e2n\u0103, din cauza coronavirusului |date=14 March 2020 |website=Digi24 |language=ro |trans-title=Parliamentarians are suspending their activity for at least a week, because of coronavirus |access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref> The same day, President [[Klaus Iohannis]] announced his decision to decree the state of emergency in Romania starting March 16.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/romania-intra-in-situatie-de-urgenta-de-la-inceputul-saptamanii-viitoare-1275543 |title=Rom\u00e2nia intr\u0103 \u00een stare de urgen\u021b\u0103 de la \u00eenceputul s\u0103pt\u0103m\u00e2nii viitoare |date=14 March 2020 |website=Digi24 |language=ro |trans-title=Romania enters in state of emergency from beginning of next week |access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn March 16, Iohannis issued the decree establishing the state of emergency in Romania for a period of 30 days and insisted that the implementation of the measures included in the decree is being made gradually.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mediafax.ro/politic/romania-a-intrat-in-stare-de-urgenta-ce-prevederi-contine-decretul-semnat-de-presedinte-18991516 |title=Rom\u00e2nia a intrat \u00een stare de urgen\u021b\u0103. Ce prevederi con\u021bine decretul semnat de pre\u0219edinte. DOCUMENTUL |date=16 March 2020 |website=Mediafax}}</ref> The schools will be closed during the state of emergency. If necessary, prices may be capped on medicines and medical equipment, on strictly necessary foods and on public utility services (electricity and heat, gas, water supply, sanitation, fuels, etc.). Also, gradual measures can be taken, if the situation gets worse, only after an evaluation of the National Committee for Special Emergency Situations. These include temporary closure of restaurants, hotels, cafes, clubs, gradual closure of borders, or limiting or prohibiting the movement of vehicles or persons in/to certain areas.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/document-romania-a-intrat-in-stare-de-urgenta-ce-prevede-decretul-semnat-de-presedintele-klaus-iohannis-1276292 |title=DOCUMENT. Rom\u00e2nia a intrat \u00een stare de urgen\u021b\u0103. Ce prevede decretul semnat de pre\u0219edintele Klaus Iohannis |date=16 March 2020 |website=Digi 24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.presidency.ro/ro/media/decret-semnat-de-presedintele-romaniei-domnul-klaus-iohannis-privind-instituirea-starii-de-urgenta-pe-teritoriul-romaniei |title=Decret semnat de Pre\u0219edintele Rom\u00e2niei, domnul Klaus Iohannis, privind instituirea st\u0103rii de urgen\u021b\u0103 pe teritoriul Rom\u00e2niei |date=16 March 2020 |website=President of Romania}}</ref> On March 19, the Parliament convened a joint online session and unanimously adopted the decree issued by Iohannis.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://stirileprotv.ro/stiri/actualitate/parlamentul-voteaza-azi-starea-de-urgenta-prima-sedinta-online-din-istoria-romaniei.html |title=Parlamentul a votat \u00een unanimitate starea de urgen\u021b\u0103. Prima \u0219edin\u021b\u0103 online din istoria Rom\u00e2niei |date=19 March 2020 |website=\u0218tirile Pro TV}}</ref>\n\nUntil March 17, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs facilitated the return to the country for 137 Romanians who were abroad, either as tourists, in transit, or in medical emergency situations and who were directly affected by the measures adopted by the states in which they were.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://stirioficiale.ro/informatii/comunicat-de-presa-privind-acordarea-de-asistenta-cetatenilor-romani-din-strainatate-in-context-covid-19-17-martie-2020 |title=Comunicat de pres\u0103 privind acordarea de asisten\u021b\u0103 cet\u0103\u021benilor rom\u00e2ni din str\u0103in\u0103tate \u00een context COVID-19 |date=17 March 2020 |website=COVID-19 \u0218tiri Oficiale}}</ref> Later that same day, the government issued its first Military Ordinance, in response to the ongoing health crisis.<ref name=\"MO1\">{{Cite web |url=http://stirioficiale.ro/hotarari/ordonanta-militara-nr-1-din-17-martie-2020 |title=Military Ordinance No.1 |last=Gogu |first=Madalina |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> Four days later, on March 21, a second Military Ordinance has been issued: no groups larger than 3 persons on the streets. Leaving home between 10 p.m. and 6 a.m. for no reason is prohibited. All shopping malls are closed, except for the sale of food, veterinary or pharmaceutical products and cleaning services. It is forbidden to enter the territory of Romania, of foreign citizens and stateless persons, except when they transit through the territory of Romania, through the transit corridor, organised by agreements with the neighboring states (more exceptions are made for other categories like: residents, family members, and others).<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/ordonanta-militara-fara-grupuri-mai-mari-de-3-persoane-pe-strazi-noi-activitati-comerciale-sunt-inchise-in-romania-1279165 |title=Ordonan\u021b\u0103 militar\u0103: F\u0103r\u0103 grupuri mai mari de 3 persoane pe str\u0103zi. P\u0103r\u0103sirea domiciliului \u00eentre orele 22-6 f\u0103r\u0103 motiv, interzis\u0103 |website=www.digi24.ro |language=ro |access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref><ref name=\"MO2\">{{Cite web |url=http://stirioficiale.ro/hotarari/ordonanta-militara-nr-2-din-21-03-2020-privind-masuri-de-prevenire-a-raspandirii-covid-19 |title=Military Ordinance No.2 |last=Gogu |first=Madalina |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n\n=== 22 March-present: First COVID-19 deaths, nationwide lockdown, Suceava quarantine, protection masks ===\n[[File:Empty street in Bucharest, Romania during coronavirus pandemic lockdown.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Empty street in [[Bucharest]] during the nationwide lockdown]]\nOn March 22, the first three deaths were reported in Romania. All three had preexisting conditions: one was on dialysis, one had terminal lung cancer, and one had diabetes.<ref name=\":3\" /><ref name=\"third-death\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/inca-un-roman-a-murit-din-cauza-conoravirusului-trei-decese-confirmate-in-romania-1279526 |title=\u00cenc\u0103 un rom\u00e2n a murit din cauza conoravirusului. Trei decese confirmate \u00een Rom\u00e2nia |date=2020-03-22 |website=Digi24 |language=ro |trans-title=Another Romanian died because of coronavirus. Three deaths confirmed in Romania |access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref> The next day, on March 23, [http://ro.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spitalul_Jude\u0163ean_de_Urgen\u0163\u0103_\u201eSf\u00e2ntul_Ioan_cel_Nou\u201d_din_Suceava Suceava's main hospital], one of the largest in the country, reported at least 34 doctors and 49 nurses infected with COVID-19, and 2 patients passing away. The hospital director was dismissed, shortly thereafter, for mismanagement.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.romaniajournal.ro/society-people/suceava-county-hospital-shuts-down-following-high-number-of-covid-19-infections-suceava-the-biggest-coronavirus-hot-zone-in-romania/|title=Suceava County Hospital shuts down following high number of COVID-19 infections. Suceava \u2013 the biggest coronavirus hot zone in Romania|website=The Romania Journal|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.archyde.com/in-romania-92-caregivers-infected-with-covid-19-in-a-single-hospital/|title=In Romania, 92 caregivers infected with Covid-19 in a single hospital|date=2020-03-26|website=archyde|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref><ref name=\"TheGuardian\">{{Cite news|vauthors=Walker S, Davies C|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/29/lack-of-testing-raises-fears-of-coronavirus-surge-in-eastern-europe|title=Lack of testing raises fears of coronavirus surge in eastern Europe|date=2020-03-29|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-04-05|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>\n\nFollowing a surge in new confirmed cases, on March 24, the government announced Military Ordinance No.3, instituting a national lockdown and calling in the [[Military of Romania|military]] to support police and Gendarmerie personnel in enforcing the new restrictions. Movement outside the home or household is prohibited, with some exceptions (work, buying food or medicine etc.). People over 65 years-old are allowed to leave their homes only between 11 a.m.-1 p.m.<ref name=\":5\" /><ref name=\"MO3\">{{Cite web |url=http://stirioficiale.ro/hotarari/ordonanta-militara-nr-3-din-24-03-2020-privind-masuri-de-prevenire-a-raspandirii-covid-19 |title=Military Ordinance No.3 |last=Gogu |first=Madalina |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref> Two days later, on March 26, the state airline [[Tarom]] suspended all internal flights.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.romania-insider.com/tarom-halts-domestic-flights-march-2020 |title=Romanian state airline Tarom suspends all internal flights |date=2020-03-26 |website=Romania Insider |access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n\nA fourth Military Ordinance has been issued on March 29, further strengthening previously imposed fines and restrictions.<ref name=\"MO4\">{{Cite web |url=http://stirioficiale.ro/hotarari/ordonanta-militara-nr-4-din-29-03-2020 |title=Military Ordinance No.4 |last=Gogu |first=Madalina |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> Two more would soon follow, issued close to the end of the next day; namely, a fifth, extending the ban on international travel,<ref name=\"MO5\">{{Cite web |url=http://stirioficiale.ro/hotarari/ordonanta-militara-nr-5-din-30-03-2020 |title=Military Ordinance No.5 |last=Gogu |first=Madalina |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> and a sixth, placing [[Suceava]], along with eight adjacent [[communes of Romania|communes]], under total quarantine,<ref name=\"MO6\">{{Cite web |url=http://stirioficiale.ro/hotarari/ordonanta-militara-nr-6-din-30-03-2020 |title=Military Ordinance No.6 |last=Gogu |first=Madalina |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref><ref name=\"SUCEAVA-1\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.romania-actualitati.ro/--136936 |title=S-a hot\u0103r\u00e2t plasarea ora\u0219ului Suceava \u0219i a 8 comune limitrofe \u00een carantin\u0103 |last=Radio Romania Actualitati |first=Radiojurnal |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> the first [[cities of Romania|Romanian city]] to be placed under complete lockdown since the start of the outbreak in late February, holding over a quarter of all infected cases,<ref name=\"SUCEAVA-1\" /> and about two thirds of all infected medical personnel.<ref name=\"SUCEAVA-2\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.romania-actualitati.ro/--136919 |title=285 de cadre medicale din Rom\u00e2nia sunt infectate cu noul coronavirus |last=Radio Romania Actualitati |first=Mihaela Dragomir |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref name=\"SUCEAVA-3\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.romania-actualitati.ro/--136951 |title=Peste 180 de cadre medicale din Suceava sunt infectate cu coronavirus |last=Radio Romania Actualitati |first=Mihaela Buculei |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> Some hospital staff have quit, others have signed a petition stating they \"are sent to death barehanded\".<ref name=\"7sur7\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.7sur7.be/monde/revolte-des-soignants-en-roumanie-envoyes-a-la-mort-les-mains-nues~ae35ffaf/ |title=R\u00e9volte des soignants en Roumanie: \u201cEnvoy\u00e9s \u00e0 la mort les mains nues\" |date=April 1, 2020 |website=7sur7.be |language=French |access-date=April 2, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn April 2, [[Harghita County|Harghita]] reported its first case, becoming the last county in Romania to report at least one case.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/singurul-judet-din-romania-fara-niciun-bolnav-de-covid-19-a-raportat-primul-caz-1285560 |title=Singurul jude\u0163 din Rom\u00e2nia f\u0103r\u0103 niciun bolnav de COVID-19 a raportat primul caz |date=2020-04-02 |website=Digi24 |language=ro |trans-title=The only county from Romania without a person sick with COVID-19 reported the first case |access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> Two days later, on April 4, a seventh Military Ordinance has been issued, further extending the national lockdown period, and placing yet [[\u021a\u0103nd\u0103rei|a second town]] under strict quarantine.<ref name=\"MO7\">{{Cite web |url=http://stirioficiale.ro/hotarari/ordonanta-militara-nr-7-din-04-04-2020 |title=Military Ordinance No.7 |last=Gogu |first=Madalina |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n\nAs of April 4, various counties and localities have started drafting local legislation requiring denizens to wear protection masks, whether professional or improvised.<ref name=\"MASKS-1\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.romania-actualitati.ro/--137265 |title=Gala\u021bi: Purtarea m\u0103\u0219tii sau e\u0219arfei pe fa\u021b\u0103, obligatorie de luni |last=Radio Romania Actualitati |first=Maria M\u0103ndi\u0163\u0103 |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref name=\"MASKS-2\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.romania-actualitati.ro/--137295 |title=Vaslui: Cet\u0103\u0163enii vor putea ie\u015fi din case doar cu nasul \u0219i gura acoperite |last=Radio Romania Actualitati |first=Radiojurnal |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref name=\"MASKS-3\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.romania-actualitati.ro/--137298 |title=Masca devine obligatorie \u0219i \u00een Simeria #Covid-19 |last=Radio Romania Actualitati |first=Ilie Pintea |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref name=\"MASKS-4\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.romania-actualitati.ro/--137312 |title=La Suceava \u0219i C\u0103l\u0103ra\u0219i nu mai po\u021bi ie\u0219i-de azi-f\u0103r\u0103 masc\u0103 ptr gur\u0103 \u0219i nas |last=Radio Romania Actualitati |first=Radiojurnal |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref name=\"MASKS-5\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.romania-actualitati.ro/--137327 |title=Purtarea m\u0103\u015ftilor de protec\u0163ie devine obligatorie \u015fi \u00een C\u0103l\u0103ra\u015fi |last=Radio Romania Actualitati |first=Florin Lep\u0103datu |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref name=\"MASKS-6\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.romania-actualitati.ro/--137381 |title=Masca devine obligatorie \u0219i \u00een jude\u021bul V\u00e2lcea |last=Radio Romania Actualitati |first=Ana-Maria C\u00eerstea |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref name=\"MASKS-7\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.romania-actualitati.ro/--137403 |title=Purtarea m\u0103\u0219tilor \u00een afara locuin\u021bei, obligatorie \u00een \u015fapte jude\u021be |last=Radio Romania Actualitati |first=Radiojurnal |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref> On April 5, [[Raed Arafat]] posted an article on his official [[Facebook]] page,<ref name=\"MASKS-ARAFAT-FB\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.facebook.com/DrRaedArafat/posts/3623588387668009 |title=Facebook post dated April 5, 2020 |last=Arafat |first=Raed |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref> later picked up by the national media and other news outlets,<ref name=\"MASKS-ARAFAT-DG24\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/sanatate/--1286999 |title=Raed Arafat, recomandare de pus \u00een practic\u0103 \u201ec\u00e2t de repede posibil\u201d: Purta\u021bi m\u0103\u0219ti! Dac\u0103 nu g\u0103si\u021bi s\u0103 cump\u0103ra\u021bi, improviza\u021bi ceva! |website=Digi24 |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref name=\"MASKS-ARAFAT-R\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.realitatea.net/stiri/actual/_5e8ab5fb188662071304b7e2 |title=Arafat, recomandare vital\u0103 pentru popula\u021bie: \"Purta\u021bi masc\u0103! Dac\u0103 o confec\u021biona\u021bi acas\u0103, sp\u0103la\u021bi-o zilnic \u0219i c\u0103lca\u021bi-o\" |website=Realitatea |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref name=\"MASKS-ARAFAT-A3\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.antena3.ro/coronavirus/--565717.html |title=Raed Arafat ne spune ce fel de masc\u0103 trebuie s\u0103 purt\u0103m. Ce s\u0103 faci dac\u0103 nu ai una |website=Antena3 |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref name=\"MASKS-ARAFAT-PROTV\">{{Cite web |url=http://stirileprotv.ro/stiri/sanatate/arafat-recomanda-purtarea-mastilor-nu-este-nevoie-de-masca-medicala-puteti-impoviza.html |title=Arafat recomand\u0103 purtarea m\u0103\u0219tilor: \u201dNu este nevoie de masc\u0103 medical\u0103, pute\u021bi improviza\u201d |website=ProTV |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref name=\"MASKS-ARAFAT-B1\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=U2IR8jqCpoY |title=ARAFAT, ANUN\u021a DESPRE PURTAREA M\u0102\u0218TILOR PE STRAD\u0102: NU E NEVOIE DE MASC\u0102 MEDICAL\u0102, PUTE\u021aI IMPROVIZA |website=B1TV |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref name=\"MASKS-ARAFAT-OBS\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fJT0xS8Xe-M |title=Raed Arafat recomand\u0103 ca toat\u0103 lumea s\u0103 poarte m\u0103\u0219ti sau s\u0103 improvizeze |website=Observator TV |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref name=\"MASKS-ARAFAT-EFM\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.europafm.ro/arafat-se-recomanda-acoperirea-nasului-si-a-gurii-in-spatiile-publice |title=Arafat: Se recomand\u0103 acoperirea nasului \u0219i a gurii \u00een spa\u0163iile publice |website=Europa FM |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref name=\"MASKS-ARAFAT-L\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.libertatea.ro/stiri/--2941853 |title=Raed Arafat recomand\u0103 s\u0103 purt\u0103m m\u0103\u0219ti pe strad\u0103: \u201ePute\u021bi improviza\u201d |website=Libertatea |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref> encouraging citizens to wear protective masks, even if homemade.<ref name=\"MASKS-ARAFAT-RI\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.romania-insider.com/ro-masks-arafat-counties-compulsory |title=Coronavirus in Romania: Head of emergency service recommends people wear masks in public places, measure compulsory in several counties |website=Romania Insider |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref name=\"MASKS-ARAFAT-HN\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.hotnews.ro/stiri-coronavirus-23790826-.htm |title=Arafat: Nu este nevoie de masca medical\u0103 c\u0103 s\u0103 va proteja\u021bi, pute\u021bi improviza |website=Hotnews |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref name=\"MASKS-ARAFAT-Z\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ziare.com/stiri/coronavirus/--1605259 |title=Arafat: Se recomanda purtatul mastii in spatiile publice. Nu trebuie sa fie medicala, puteti improviza |website=Ziare |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref name=\"MASKS-ARAFAT-N\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.news.ro/social/1922405105212020041619325868-1922405105212020041619325868 |title=Arafat: Se recomand\u0103 purtatul m\u0103\u015ftii sau al altor forme de material de protec\u0163ie pentru nas \u015fi gur\u0103, \u00een spa\u0163iile publice / Ar fi bine s\u0103 \u00eencepem s\u0103 aplic\u0103m aceast\u0103 practic\u0103 c\u00e2t de repede posibil / Nu este nevoie de masca medical\u0103, pute\u0163i improviza |website=News.ro |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref> Prime minister [[Ludovic Orban]], on the other hand, expressed doubts not only concerning the safety of homemade improvisations, but also about the necessary logistics for successfully implementing such a large scale operation, inasmuch as the demand would greatly outweigh the extant offer currently available on the market.<ref name=\"MASKS-ORBAN-DG24\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/sanatate/--1287155 |title=Orban, despre legile cu privire la purtarea m\u0103\u015ftilor: Nu po\u0163i s\u0103 impui obligativitate c\u00e2t timp nu sunt accesibile pentru cet\u0103\u0163eni |website=Digi24 |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref name=\"MASKS-ORBAN-PROTV\">{{Cite web |url=http://stirileprotv.ro/stiri/politic/orban-despre-masti-nu-poti-sa-impui-obligativitate-daca-nu-sunt-accesibile-pentru-cetateni.html |title=Orban, despre m\u0103\u015fti: Nu po\u0163i s\u0103 impui obligativitate dac\u0103 nu sunt accesibile pentru cet\u0103\u0163eni |website=ProTV |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref name=\"MASKS-ORBAN-A\">{{Cite web |url=http://adevarul.ro/news/eveniment/-1_5e8a2e145163ec427177039a |title=Orban, despre purtarea m\u0103\u015ftilor: \u00cen perioada actual\u0103 \u00een care efectiv aceste m\u0103\u015fti nu se g\u0103sesc sau se g\u0103sesc la pre\u0163uri foarte mari, nu po\u0163i impune o astfel de obliga\u0163ie |website=Adevarul |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref name=\"MASKS-ORBAN-SPS\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.stiripesurse.ro/__1449627.html |title=Ludovic Orban, despre acoperirea obligatorie a nasului \u0219i a gurii: Improviza\u021biile nu cred c\u0103 fac bine |website=Stiri pe surse |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref name=\"MASKS-ORBAN-Z\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ziare.com/social/administratia/--1605683 |title=Tot mai multe judete sau localitati introduc purtarea obligatorie a mastilor in public. Iata situatia la zi |website=Ziare |language=ro-RO |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n\n== Cases ==\nOn March 14, 18 days after the diagnosis of the first case of infection with [[SARS-CoV-2]], Romania surpassed the threshold of 100 confirmed cases. 49% of those diagnosed were outside the country prior to diagnosis.<ref name=\"schitea\">{{Cite web |url=https://raportuldegarda.ro/articol/analiza-primii-100-pacienti-covid19-romania-ce-am-invatat-pana-acum-ce-trebuie-sa-facem-in-continuare/ |title=ANALIZ\u0102. Primii 100 de pacien\u021bi cu #COVID19 din Rom\u00e2nia. Ce am \u00eenv\u0103\u021bat p\u00e2n\u0103 acum \u0219i ce trebuie s\u0103 facem \u00een continuare? |last=Schitea, Ruxandra |date=15 March 2020 |website=Raportul de Gard\u0103}}</ref> In 35% of cases, patients were previously in [[Italy]], the country most affected by the pandemic in the [[European Union]]. These people were the main sources of transmission of the virus to the other 50%, in a single situation being unable to identify a suggestive epidemiological context for the diagnosed patient.<ref name=\"schitea\" /> Two diagnosed people (cases #17 and #27) were responsible for infecting 22% of the number of patients.<ref name=\"schitea\" /> This situation was possible because each of them hid from authorities, in the initial phase, the fact that they had previously travelled to an area at risk of infection, which delayed the initiation of the epidemiological investigation and exposed more people to the risk of infection. More than half of the cases (54%) were diagnosed in three counties: [[Bucharest]], [[Timi\u0219 County|Timi\u0219]] and [[Hunedoara County|Hunedoara]].<ref name=\"schitea\" /> A patient out of three was diagnosed in Bucharest. Only six of the first 100 infected Romanian patients were older than 70, the age at which coronavirus often poses serious health problems, especially when the infected one also suffers from associated diseases.<ref name=\"schitea\" /> Of the first 100 patients, only one case was serious, requiring ICU admission, while nine patients recovered, and 90 had mild to moderate symptoms.<ref name=\"schitea\" />\n\nOn March 15, the Ministry of Health stopped publishing data on sex, age, origin, contacts and other details of individual cases. The information about the new cases were communicated in two newsletters per day, one at 10 a.m., the other at 6 p.m.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.hotnews.ro/stiri-coronavirus-23726080-coronavirus-romania-alte-8-noi-cazuri-bilantul-imbolnavirilor-131-astazi-autoritatile-anunta-noile-cazuri-singura-data.htm |title=UPDATE Coronavirus \u00een Rom\u00e2nia: 16 noi cazuri diagnosticate duminic\u0103. Bilan\u021bul \u00eemboln\u0103virilor - 139 |last=Neagu, Alina |date=15 March 2020 |website=HotNews.ro}}</ref> From March 19 onward, the reporting of the new confirmed cases was done only once a day, at 1 p.m.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/bilantul-noilor-cazuri-de-coronavirus-in-romania-va-fi-anuntat-o-singura-data-pe-zi-1277890 |title=Bilan\u021bul noilor cazuri de coronavirus \u00een Rom\u00e2nia va fi anun\u021bat o singur\u0103 dat\u0103 pe zi |date=19 March 2020 |website=Digi 24}}</ref>\n\nOn March 24, prime minister [[Ludovic Orban]] stated the Government's goal to eventually increase the testing capacity to well over 2500 people a day,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.romania-insider.com/coronavirus-romania-testing|title=Coronavirus in Romania: Govt. prefers no testing instead of quick testing|website=Romania Insider|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> which seems to have been achieved by early April.<ref name=\"Statista\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.statista.com/statistics/1103934/covid-19-tests-romania|title=Number of coronavirus (COVID-19) tests taken in Romania from March to April 2020|website=Statista|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\n<div style=\"max-height: 500px; overflow-y: scroll; padding-right: 20px\">\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable mw-collapsible\" style=\"text-align:left; font-size:90%\"\n|+ style=\"font-size:120%\" | {{nowrap|List of COVID-19 confirmed cases in Romania}}\n|-\n! # !! Date (2020) !! Status !! Source of infection !! Origin of infection !! Detection location !! Sex !! Age !! Notes !! Source\n|-\n! 1\n| 26 Feb. \n| {{Success|Recovered}}<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.libertatea.ro/stiri/primul-caz-coronavirus-confirmat-romania-2896137 |title=B\u0103rbatul din Gorj care s-a vindecat de coronavirus poate fi externat, dar nu se poate \u00eentoarce \u00een familie |last=Anton |first=Cristian |last2=Ochianu |first2=